    "short_description": "BBQ, bebop, and baseball history in KC's legendary jazz corridor.",
    "long_description": "The 18th & Vine Historic Jazz District is the beating heart of Kansas City's African American cultural heritage. This compact, walkable neighborhood gave birth to the Kansas City jazz sound and was home to some of the greatest musicians in American history. \n\nBegin with a pilgrimage to Arthur Bryant's for legendary slow-smoked barbecue, then dive into the dual museums at the corner of 18th and Vine — the Negro Leagues Baseball Museum and the American Jazz Museum share a building and tell two of America's most important and overlooked stories. \n\nCap the evening at The Blue Room, one of the country's great surviving jazz clubs, where live music fills the air just as it did in the district's golden age.",
